# Style Remover Chrome Extension

## Description

Style Remover is a Google Chrome extension that removes specific CSS styles from web pages. It targets and removes the following styles:

- Any `blur` filter effect (e.g., `filter: blur(4px)`, `filter: blur(10px)`, etc.)
- `user-select: none;`

This extension is useful for improving readability and enabling text selection on websites that may have intentionally blurred content or disabled text selection.

## Features

- Automatically removes all blur effects from elements, regardless of blur intensity
- Enables text selection on elements where it was disabled
- Works on page load and continues to monitor for dynamically added content

## Installation

1. Clone this repository or download the source code.
2. Open Google Chrome and navigate to `chrome://extensions`.
3. Enable "Developer mode" in the top right corner.
4. Click "Load unpacked" and select the directory containing the extension files.

## Usage

Once installed, the extension will automatically run on all web pages. No further action is required from the user.

## Files

- `manifest.json`: Configuration file for the Chrome extension
- `content.js`: Contains the main logic for removing styles

## Contributing

Contributions to improve the extension are welcome. Please feel free to submit a pull request or open an issue to discuss potential changes/additions.

